FINAL SOC ARCHITECTURE (FROZEN BASELINE):

                +------------------+
                | AXI MASTER TB    |
                +--------+---------+
                         |
                  AXI Interconnect
                         |
       +-----------------+-----------------+
       |                                   |
 +-----+------+                    +-------+------+
 | AXI SRAM   |                    | AXI -> APB    |
 +------------+                    +-------+------+
                                           |
                   +-----------------------+--------------------+
                   |              |            |                |
                 GPIO IP       UART IP       SPI IP          DMA CTRL


SOC ROADMAP:

PHASE 1 - AXI Basics

PHASE 2 - AXI Interconnect

PHASE 3 - AXI -> APB Bridge

PHASE 4 - GPIO/UART/SPI/DMA peripherals

PHASE 5 - Full-system integration

This progression is extremely logical.

1. FREEZE BUS TYPES

This is the most important decision

| Block          | Bus Type               |
| -------------- | ---------------------- |
| AXI MASTER TB  | AXI4-Lite              |
| AXI SRAM       | AXI4-Lite Slave        |
| AXI->APB Bridge| AXI slave + APB master |
| GPIO           | APB Slave              |
| UART           | APB Slave              |
| SPI            | APB Slave              |
| DMA CTRL       | APB Slave              |

2. FREEZE DATA WIDTHS

Keep this consistent everywhere initially

| Signal      | Width  |
| ----------- | ------ |
| AXI address | 32-bit |
| AXI data    | 32-bit |
| APB address | 32-bit |
| APB data    | 32-bit |

Why?

avoids conversion logic now
simpler bridge design
easier scoreboard reuse

3. FREEZE AXI VERSION

Use: AXI4-Lite

NOT full AXI4 initially.

Why?

single beat only
no burst complexity
easier learning
still teaches VALID/READY properly

Later you can evolve.

4. FREEZE APB VERSION

Use:

APB3-style simple slave

Current GPIO/MEMORY already align closely.

5. FREEZE MEMORY MAP (VERY IMPORTANT)

This avoids future conflicts.

AXI ADDRESS MAP:

           Region	     Address Range Target
0x0000_0000 -> 0x0000_FFFF	AXI SRAM
0x1000_0000 -> 0x1000_FFFF	AXI->APB Bridge

APB PERIPHERAL MAP

Behind bridge:

Peripheral	Base Address
GPIO	        0x1000_0000
UART	        0x1000_1000
SPI	        0x1000_2000
DMA CTRL	0x1000_3000


6. FREEZE GPIO REGISTER MAP
Register	Offset
GPIO_DATA	0x00
GPIO_DIR	0x04


7. FREEZE UART REGISTER MAP (future)
Register	Offset
TXDATA	        0x00
RXDATA	        0x04
STATUS	        0x08
CONTROL	        0x0C


8. FREEZE SPI REGISTER MAP (future)
Register	Offset
TXDATA    	0x00
RXDATA	        0x04
STATUS	        0x08
CONTROL	        0x0C


9. FREEZE DMA CTRL REGISTERS
Register	Offset
SRC_ADDR	0x00
DST_ADDR	0x04
LENGTH	        0x08
CONTROL	        0x0C
STATUS	        0x10

10. FREEZE VERIFICATION STRATEGY

This is equally important.

Component	Verification Style
AXI Master	active driver
APB peripherals	passive DUTs
Scoreboard	reference model compare
Memory model	shadow reference memory
Logging	        centralized PASS/FAIL

